name: Version 2.2.1
body: Incorporates PR #45 for multi-threaded CWL reading.

name: Version 2.2.0
body: Adds multi-threaded reading for Cloudwatch Logs.

name: Version 2.1.1
body: Fixes a packaging error. See PR #43 .

name: Version 2.1.0
body: Adds multi-threaded reads for S3 locations

name: Version 2.0.0
body:
Major changes:
* Python 2 support has ended
* Version 3 of VPC Flow Logs are now supported

name: Support S3 in the CLI when using "assume role"
body: Incorporates PR #33, which fixes a bug with the command line utility and S3 log retrieval.

name: Support VPC Flow Logs in S3
body: Incorporates PR #31, which adds support for retrieving VPC Flow Logs from S3.

name: Support undocumented millisecond timestamps
body: Incorporates PR #30 to support millisecond timestamps that are in some newer flow records.

name: Catch PaginationError
body: Incorporates #28 to deal with the CWL server returning the same NextToken twice.

name: Filter by default, limit records returned by CLI
Version 0.3
body: Fixed #14 - `FlowLogsReader` now respects the `AWS_DEFAULT_REGION` environment variable or `~/.aws/config` file when called without the `region_name` parameter.

name: Version 0.2
body: Switches to the `FilterLogEvents` API to simplify pagination.
